#: ../app/views/localization/constituency_types.html.erb:4
msgid "Dáil Eireann"
msgstr ""

#: ../app/views/localization/constituency_types.html.erb:5
msgid ""
"Dáil Éireann is the lower house of the Oireachtas, but is the source of almost all legislation in Ireland. It consists of no less than one Teachta Dála (TD) for every thirty thousand citizens. TDs are full time public representatives and are responsible for representing their constituents on the national level.\n"
"\n"
"The Dáil elects members of the Cabinet who ensure that the policies of the Government are carried out. They are assisted by the various Ministers of State in this. The Dáil also has a number of committees which scrutinise legislation proposed to them.\n"
"\n"
"TDs are the people you should contact if you have questions or concerns about national issues. Examples would be the Budget, taxation, Health policy or other nationwide initiatives."
msgstr ""

#: ../app/views/localization/constituency_types.html.erb:10
msgid "European Parliament"
msgstr ""

#: ../app/views/localization/constituency_types.html.erb:11
msgid ""
"MEPs serve in the European Parliament, the directly elected parliamentary institution of the European Union (EU). Together with the Council of the European Union (the Council) and the European Commission, it exercises the legislative function of the EU.\n"
"\n"
"MEPs are the people you should contact if you have questions or concerns about european issues. Examples would be EU treaties and Union wide agreements such as the Common Agricultural Policy or Fisheries Policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../app/views/localization/constituency_types.html.erb:14
msgid "Local Electoral Area"
msgstr ""

#: ../app/views/localization/constituency_types.html.erb:15
msgid ""
"City and County Councils exist to represent the interest of large communities. Whilst the role of a Councillor is similar to that of a TD or MEP in that they represent the views of their constituents, they are slightly different in the sense that it is primarily a part-time function, so most Councillors will also have a \"regular\" job.\n"
"\n"
"County and City Councils are elected from a number of Local Electoral Areas.\n"
"\n"
"Councillors are the people you should contact if you have questions or concerns about local issues. Examples would include problems with local infrastructure like refuse collection or damaged facilities."
msgstr ""

